Pico kernel

Inside docs folder contains The Definitive Guide to ARM Cortex -M0 and Cortex-M0+ Processors. With useful information about Cortex-M0+.
The RP2040 datasheet also provides information about the SoC. 

The Getting started with Raspberry Pi Pico - provides information on how to debug and the setup required to use Picoprobe alongside VSCode.
It will require the Cortex-Debug extension as described. https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=marus25.cortex-debug

Dependencies

- cmake version 3.15
- python3 interpreter
- arm-none-eabi-gcc
- arm-none-eabi-gdb (gdb-multiarch may also work)

- openocd - compatible with pi pico

Raspberry Pi Documentation

https://www.raspberrypi.com/documentation/microcontrollers/c_sdk.html


To compile

cd build
cmake ..
make -j4

This will create the file firmware.uf2 used to manually flash the board.